{
  "text": "Mitchell and [CITATION_1] tested the inactivation of cell cultured EBOV diluted in human serum samples (1/10, final concentration of 5 to 7 logs 10 plaque-forming unit (PFU)/ml). Complete inactivation of the virus in serum samples occurred at 60 °C, but not at 45 °C or 56 °C. The time required to inactivate 5 logs PFU/ml at 60 °C was 22 min. [CITATION_2] achieved the inactivation of EBOV by heating it at 75 °C for 30 min.",
